ecpBoardTable.name: ecpBoardTable
ecpBoardTable.description: This table contains Extended Control Processor (ECP) board information.

ecpBoardEntry.name: ecpBoardEntry
ecpBoardEntry.description: This entry contains Extended Control Processor (ECP) board information

ecpBoardIndex.name: ecpBoardIndex
ecpBoardIndex.description: This is the Extended Control Processor board index within the management station.

ecpBoardVersion.name: ecpBoardVersion
ecpBoardVersion.description: This is the version number of this Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpBoardSerialNumber.name: ecpBoardSerialNumber
ecpBoardSerialNumber.description: This is the serial number of this Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpBoardOtherEcpPresent.name: ecpBoardOtherEcpPresent
ecpBoardOtherEcpPresent.description: This is the other ECP board present indicator for this Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpBoardEsiPresent.name: ecpBoardEsiPresent
ecpBoardEsiPresent.description: This is the External Synchronization Interface (ESI) present indicator for this Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfTable.name: ecpSerialIfTable
ecpSerialIfTable.description: This table contains the serial port interface information for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfEntry.name: ecpSerialIfEntry
ecpSerialIfEntry.description: This entry contains the serial port interface information for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortIndex.name: ecpSerialIfPortIndex
ecpSerialIfPortIndex.description: This is the serial port interface index for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortType.name: ecpSerialIfPortType
ecpSerialIfPortType.description: This is the serial port interface type for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortSpeed.name: ecpSerialIfPortSpeed
ecpSerialIfPortSpeed.description: This is the serial port interface speed for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfFlowType.name: ecpSerialIfFlowType
ecpSerialIfFlowType.description: This is the serial port interface flow control for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortBits.name: ecpSerialIfPortBits
ecpSerialIfPortBits.description: This is the serial port interface character size for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortStopBits.name: ecpSerialIfPortStopBits
ecpSerialIfPortStopBits.description: This is the serial port interface stop bit count for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpSerialIfPortParity.name: ecpSerialIfPortParity
ecpSerialIfPortParity.description: This is the serial port interface character parity for this port on the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpAlarmTable.name: ecpAlarmTable
ecpAlarmTable.description: A table of switch alarm definitions and configuration.

ecpAlarmEntry.name: ecpAlarmEntry
ecpAlarmEntry.description: A table entry containing switch alarm definitions.

ecpAlarmStatus.name: ecpAlarmStatus
ecpAlarmStatus.description: The status of this alarm entry. An alarm becomes active if the underlying condition is detected. For power supplies, the input failed alarm condition is asserted if the input voltage is not within the nominal range for the supply. This does not necessarily mean that an ouput failure will result. A power supply output failure condition is asserted if any power supply is failing or if it is physically removed. Power supply output alarms are only applicable to switches with multiple power supplies. Fan bank and temperature sensor failures are applicable only to switches with the appropriate sensing capabilities. Link and spans failures are applicable to all switches.

ecpAlarmMinorCategory.name: ecpAlarmMinorCategory
ecpAlarmMinorCategory.description: This object indicates whether a minor alarm is triggered when this event occurs.

ecpAlarmMajorCategory.name: ecpAlarmMajorCategory
ecpAlarmMajorCategory.description: This object indicates whether a major alarm is triggered when this event occurs.

ecpAlarmReset.name: ecpAlarmReset
ecpAlarmReset.description: The manager may set this to the value zero to cancel a current alarm. This is useful for silencing alarms triggered via edge detection. If this variable is readable, then the alarm is resettable.

ecpAlarmMajorRelayState.name: ecpAlarmMajorRelayState
ecpAlarmMajorRelayState.description: This object indicates the current state of the major alarm relay. If one or more of the alarms (ecpAlarmType) that are defined major (ecpAlarmMajorCategory) are currently active (ecpAlarmStatus), this object will be on(1).

ecpAlarmMinorRelayState.name: ecpAlarmMinorRelayState
ecpAlarmMinorRelayState.description: This object indicates the current state of the minor alarm relay. Ifone or mote of the alarms (ecpAlarmType) that are defined minor (ecpAlarmMinorCategory) are currently active (ecpAlarmStatus), this object will be on(1).

ecpAlarmRelayTable.name: ecpAlarmRelayTable
ecpAlarmRelayTable.description: This table contains the alarm relay definitions for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpAlarmRelayEntry.name: ecpAlarmRelayEntry
ecpAlarmRelayEntry.description: This entry contains the alarm relay definitions for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpAlarmRelayIndex.name: ecpAlarmRelayIndex
ecpAlarmRelayIndex.description: This is the index of the alarm relay on the Extended Control Processor (ECP). The Raven ECP has 5 addressable alarm relays (1-5).

ecpAlarmRelayFunction.name: ecpAlarmRelayFunction
ecpAlarmRelayFunction.description: This is the alarm function associated with an alarm relay on the Extended Control Processor (ECP). An alarm relay may either be unused, assigned to the major alarm, or assigned to the minor alarm.

ecpAlarmRelayState.name: ecpAlarmRelayState
ecpAlarmRelayState.description: This is the current state of the alarm relay on the Extended Control Processor (ECP). The state 'on' means that the alarm relay is activated; the state 'off' means that it is deactivated.

ecpSwMainTable.name: ecpSwMainTable
ecpSwMainTable.description: The table contains the Extended Control Processor (ECP) information maintained by the control software.

ecpSwMainEntry.name: ecpSwMainEntry
ecpSwMainEntry.description: This entry contains the Extended Control Processor (ECP) information maintained by the control software.

ecpName.name: ecpName
ecpName.description: This is the system name of this Extended Control Processor (ECP) platform.

ecpHardwareVersion.name: ecpHardwareVersion
ecpHardwareVersion.description: This is the hardware version of the Extended Control Processor (ECP) platform.

ecpSoftwareVersion.name: ecpSoftwareVersion
ecpSoftwareVersion.description: This is the software version of the Extended Control Processor (ECP) control software. The version is encoded into 6 hex characters. Version 1.2.3 would be 0x010203.

ecpSoftwareVersionText.name: ecpSoftwareVersionText
ecpSoftwareVersionText.description: This is the software version text of the Extended Control Processor (ECP) control software. This object contains information regarding the software configuration that was used to build this software.

ecpType.name: ecpType
ecpType.description: This is the type of the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpOperatingStatus.name: ecpOperatingStatus
ecpOperatingStatus.description: This is the software status of this Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpProtocolType.name: ecpProtocolType
ecpProtocolType.description: The transfer protocol that is used when upgrading the software, saving/restoring the CDB, etc. on this Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpTimeZone.name: ecpTimeZone
ecpTimeZone.description: The TimeZone configured for this Extended Control Processor (ECP). This variable follows the POSIX standard 1003.1-1988 for the format of the TZ environment variable. In particular, it is general enough to specify the rules for converting from Standard to Daylight Savings time for most timezones of the world. By default, the ECP has the rules built in for the following timezones: EST5EDT CST6CDT MST7MDT PST8PDT AKST9AKDT. Locales outside of these timezones will need to supply the appropriate rule for switching between Daylight and Standard time.

ecpGMTime.name: ecpGMTime
ecpGMTime.description: The Extended Control Processor's (ECP's) notion of Greenwich Mean Time. Linked to hrSystemDate. Offset part of time spec, if supplied, is considered an error.

ecpUptime.name: ecpUptime
ecpUptime.description: This is the amount of time that the Extended Control Processor (ECP) control software has been running, in hundredths of a second.

ecpModeChangeTime.name: ecpModeChangeTime
ecpModeChangeTime.description: This is the time that the Extended Control Processor (ECP) control software has switched to the current operating mode.

ecpOtherEcpStatus.name: ecpOtherEcpStatus
ecpOtherEcpStatus.description: This is the software status of the other Extended Control Processor (ECP) from the viewpoint of this ECP.

ecpExternalInput1.name: ecpExternalInput1
ecpExternalInput1.description: This is the state of External Input #1 from the viewpoint of the Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpExternalInput2.name: ecpExternalInput2
ecpExternalInput2.description: This is the state of External Input #2 from the viewpoint of the Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpExternalInput3.name: ecpExternalInput3
ecpExternalInput3.description: This is the state of External Input #3 from the viewpoint of the Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpExternalInput4.name: ecpExternalInput4
ecpExternalInput4.description: This is the state of External Input #4 from the viewpoint of the Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpExternalInput5.name: ecpExternalInput5
ecpExternalInput5.description: This is the state of External Input #5 from the viewpoint of the Extended Control Processor (ECP).

ecpNetIfTable.name: ecpNetIfTable
ecpNetIfTable.description: This table contains the network interface information for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpNetIfEntry.name: ecpNetIfEntry
ecpNetIfEntry.description: This entry contains the network interface information for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpNetIfIndex.name: ecpNetIfIndex
ecpNetIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

ecpNetIfDescr.name: ecpNetIfDescr
ecpNetIfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

ecpNetIfPhysAddress.name: ecpNetIfPhysAddress
ecpNetIfPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

ecpNetIfAdminStatus.name: ecpNetIfAdminStatus
ecpNetIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface.

ecpNetIfOperStatus.name: ecpNetIfOperStatus
ecpNetIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface.

ecpNetIfLastChange.name: ecpNetIfLastChange
ecpNetIfLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

ecpNetIfIpAddr.name: ecpNetIfIpAddr
ecpNetIfIpAddr.description: The IP address associated with this network interface.

ecpNetIfIpMask.name: ecpNetIfIpMask
ecpNetIfIpMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

ecpNetIfIpBcastAddr.name: ecpNetIfIpBcastAddr
ecpNetIfIpBcastAddr.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

ecpNetIfStatsTable.name: ecpNetIfStatsTable
ecpNetIfStatsTable.description: This table contains the network interface statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpNetIfStatsEntry.name: ecpNetIfStatsEntry
ecpNetIfStatsEntry.description: This entry contains the network interface statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpNetIfInOctets.name: ecpNetIfInOctets
ecpNetIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

ecpNetIfInUcastPkts.name: ecpNetIfInUcastPkts
ecpNetIfInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

ecpNetIfInNUcastPkts.name: ecpNetIfInNUcastPkts
ecpNetIfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

ecpNetIfInDiscards.name: ecpNetIfInDiscards
ecpNetIfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

ecpNetIfInErrors.name: ecpNetIfInErrors
ecpNetIfInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

ecpNetIfInUnknownProtos.name: ecpNetIfInUnknownProtos
ecpNetIfInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

ecpNetIfOutOctets.name: ecpNetIfOutOctets
ecpNetIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

ecpNetIfOutUcastPkts.name: ecpNetIfOutUcastPkts
ecpNetIfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

ecpNetIfOutNUcastPkts.name: ecpNetIfOutNUcastPkts
ecpNetIfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

ecpNetIfOutDiscards.name: ecpNetIfOutDiscards
ecpNetIfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

ecpNetIfOutErrors.name: ecpNetIfOutErrors
ecpNetIfOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

ecpNetIfOutQLen.name: ecpNetIfOutQLen
ecpNetIfOutQLen.description: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).

ecpIpStatsTable.name: ecpIpStatsTable
ecpIpStatsTable.description: This table contains the Internet protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIpStatsEntry.name: ecpIpStatsEntry
ecpIpStatsEntry.description: This entry contains the Internet protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIpInReceives.name: ecpIpInReceives
ecpIpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

ecpIpInHdrErrors.name: ecpIpInHdrErrors
ecpIpInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

ecpIpInAddrErrors.name: ecpIpInAddrErrors
ecpIpInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP Gateways and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

ecpIpForwDatagrams.name: ecpIpForwDatagrams
ecpIpForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP Gateways, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source- Route option processing was successful.

ecpIpInUnknownProtos.name: ecpIpInUnknownProtos
ecpIpInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

ecpIpInDiscards.name: ecpIpInDiscards
ecpIpInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

ecpIpInDelivers.name: ecpIpInDelivers
ecpIpInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

ecpIpOutRequests.name: ecpIpOutRequests
ecpIpOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

ecpIpOutDiscards.name: ecpIpOutDiscards
ecpIpOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

ecpIpOutNoRoutes.name: ecpIpOutNoRoutes
ecpIpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagarms which a host cannot route because all of its default gateways are down.

ecpIpReasmReqds.name: ecpIpReasmReqds
ecpIpReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

ecpIpReasmOKs.name: ecpIpReasmOKs
ecpIpReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully re- assembled.

ecpIpReasmFails.name: ecpIpReasmFails
ecpIpReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re- assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

ecpIpFragOKs.name: ecpIpFragOKs
ecpIpFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

ecpIpFragFails.name: ecpIpFragFails
ecpIpFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

ecpIpFragCreates.name: ecpIpFragCreates
ecpIpFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

ecpIpRouteTable.name: ecpIpRouteTable
ecpIpRouteTable.description: This table contains the Internet Protocol routing entries for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIpRouteEntry.name: ecpIpRouteEntry
ecpIpRouteEntry.description: This entry contains the Internet Protocol routing data for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIpRouteDest.name: ecpIpRouteDest
ecpIpRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

ecpIpRouteIfIndex.name: ecpIpRouteIfIndex
ecpIpRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ecpIpRouteNextHop.name: ecpIpRouteNextHop
ecpIpRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)

ecpIpRouteMetric1.name: ecpIpRouteMetric1
ecpIpRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ecpIpRouteType.name: ecpIpRouteType
ecpIpRouteType.description: The type of route. Note that the values direct(3) and indirect(4) refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipRouteTable object. That is, it effectively dissasociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipRouteType object.

ecpIpRouteMask.name: ecpIpRouteMask
ecpIpRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent ipRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the ipRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

ecpIcmpStatsTable.name: ecpIcmpStatsTable
ecpIcmpStatsTable.description: This table contains the Internet Control Message Protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIcmpStatsEntry.name: ecpIcmpStatsEntry
ecpIcmpStatsEntry.description: This entry contains the Internet Control Message Protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpIcmpInMsgs.name: ecpIcmpInMsgs
ecpIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpInErrors.

ecpIcmpInErrors.name: ecpIcmpInErrors
ecpIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

ecpIcmpInDestUnreach.name: ecpIcmpInDestUnreach
ecpIcmpInDestUnreach.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

ecpIcmpInTimeExcds.name: ecpIcmpInTimeExcds
ecpIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

ecpIcmpInParmProbs.name: ecpIcmpInParmProbs
ecpIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

ecpIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: ecpIcmpInSrcQuenchs
ecpIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

ecpIcmpInRedirects.name: ecpIcmpInRedirects
ecpIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages received.

ecpIcmpInEchos.name: ecpIcmpInEchos
ecpIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received.

ecpIcmpInEchoReps.name: ecpIcmpInEchoReps
ecpIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages received.

ecpIcmpInTimestamps.name: ecpIcmpInTimestamps
ecpIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages received.

ecpIcmpInTimestampReps.name: ecpIcmpInTimestampReps
ecpIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

ecpIcmpInaddrMasks.name: ecpIcmpInaddrMasks
ecpIcmpInaddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

ecpIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: ecpIcmpInAddrMaskReps
ecpIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

ecpIcmpOutMsgs.name: ecpIcmpOutMsgs
ecpIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

ecpIcmpOutErrors.name: ecpIcmpOutErrors
ecpIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter's value.

ecpIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: ecpIcmpOutDestUnreachs
ecpIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: ecpIcmpOutTimeExcds
ecpIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutParmProbs.name: ecpIcmpOutParmProbs
ecpIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: ecpIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
ecpIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutRedirects.name: ecpIcmpOutRedirects
ecpIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

ecpIcmpOutEchos.name: ecpIcmpOutEchos
ecpIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutEchoReps.name: ecpIcmpOutEchoReps
ecpIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutTimestamps.name: ecpIcmpOutTimestamps
ecpIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: ecpIcmpOutTimestampReps
ecpIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: ecpIcmpOutAddrMasks
ecpIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

ecpIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: ecpIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
ecpIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

ecpTcpStatsTable.name: ecpTcpStatsTable
ecpTcpStatsTable.description: This table contains the Transmission Control Protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpTcpStatsEntry.name: ecpTcpStatsEntry
ecpTcpStatsEntry.description: This entry contains the Transmission Control Protocol statistics for the Extended Control Processor (ECP) board.

ecpTcpActiveOpens.name: ecpTcpActiveOpens
ecpTcpActiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-SENT state from the CLOSED state.

ecpTcpPassiveOpens.name: ecpTcpPassiveOpens
ecpTcpPassiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-RCVD state from the LISTEN state.

ecpTcpAttemptFails.name: ecpTcpAttemptFails
ecpTcpAttemptFails.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SYN-SENT state or the SYN-RCVD state, plus the number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the LISTEN state from the SYN-RCVD state.

ecpTcpEstabResets.name: ecpTcpEstabResets
ecpTcpEstabResets.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the ESTABLISHED state or the CLOSE-WAIT state.

ecpTcpCurrEstab.name: ecpTcpCurrEstab
ecpTcpCurrEstab.description: The number of TCP connections for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED or CLOSE- WAIT.

ecpTcpInSegs.name: ecpTcpInSegs
ecpTcpInSegs.description: The total number of segments received, including those received in error. This count includes segments received on currently established connections.

ecpTcpOutSegs.name: ecpTcpOutSegs
ecpTcpOutSegs.description: The total number of segments sent, including those on current connections but excluding those containing only retransmitted octets.
